11.Literal: A Digital Edition of W. H. Auden's Letters to Stella Musulin. The collection contains the letters and literary papers sent by British-American poet W. H. Auden to Welsh-Austrian writer Stella Musulin in the period 1960-1973; private photographs of W. H. Auden and Chester Kallman; correspondence and papers related to Stella Musulin's biographical work on W. H. Auden; Stella Musulin's Auden memoirs "In Retrospect" and "The Years in Austria". The collection has been edited in the context of an FWF-funded, three-year project at the Austrian Centre for Digital Humanities and Cultural Heritage.

data.Name: clarin-vlo
data.Label: CLARIN VLO
data.Notes:
Denotes Collections or Resources in ARCHE that should be harvested by the CLARIN Virtual Language Observatory (VLO, https://vlo.clarin.eu).
Criteria for inclusion: the object should be a language resource, i. e. conform to the criteria defined by the Class E33 'Linguistic Object' in CIDOC CRM.
From the definition of E33: the set comprises identifiable expressions in natural language or languages. Instances can be expressed in many ways: e.g. as written texts, recorded speech or sign language. They are independent from the medium or method by which they are expressed. Expressions in formal languages, such as computer code or mathematical formulae, are not part of the set. (http://www.cidoc-crm.org/Entity/e33-linguistic-object/version-6.1)
Examples: a photograph of an inscription, a text document, a scan of a text document, a dictionary file, a corpus, an audio recording etc.

data.Name: kulturpool
data.Label: Kulturpool
data.Notes:
Denotes any Collections or Resources in ARCHE that should be harvested by Kulturpool (http://www.kulturpool.at) which is further harvested by Europeana (https://www.europeana.eu). 
To have a better understanding of what should be included, have a look at the Europeana Content Strategy (https://pro.europeana.eu/post/europeana-content-strategy).
Criteria for inlcusion: relation to cultural heritage, high-quality content, open data (metadata has to point to a freely accessible digital object), relation to Europe.

data.Name: clarin-vlo
data.Label: CLARIN VLO
data.Notes:
Denotes Collections or Resources in ARCHE that should be harvested by the CLARIN Virtual Language Observatory (VLO, https://vlo.clarin.eu).
Criteria for inclusion: the object should be a language resource, i. e. conform to the criteria defined by the Class E33 'Linguistic Object' in CIDOC CRM.
From the definition of E33: the set comprises identifiable expressions in natural language or languages. Instances can be expressed in many ways: e.g. as written texts, recorded speech or sign language. They are independent from the medium or method by which they are expressed. Expressions in formal languages, such as computer code or mathematical formulae, are not part of the set. (http://www.cidoc-crm.org/Entity/e33-linguistic-object/version-6.1)
Examples: a photograph of an inscription, a text document, a scan of a text document, a dictionary file, a corpus, an audio recording etc.

data.Name: kulturpool
data.Label: Kulturpool
data.Notes:
Denotes any Collections or Resources in ARCHE that should be harvested by Kulturpool (http://www.kulturpool.at) which is further harvested by Europeana (https://www.europeana.eu). 
To have a better understanding of what should be included, have a look at the Europeana Content Strategy (https://pro.europeana.eu/post/europeana-content-strategy).
Criteria for inlcusion: relation to cultural heritage, high-quality content, open data (metadata has to point to a freely accessible digital object), relation to Europe.
